message.content: We let $g$ be the number of girls on the chess team. Then $b = 26 - g$ is the number of boys on the chess team. The number of girls who attended the last meeting is $g/2,$ and the number of boys who attended the last meeting is $26 - g.$ Therefore, $16 = g/2 + 26 - g,$ or $g = \boxed{12}.$
